String s = "Ayush";
int count = 0;   // Step 0: initialize counter

// Step 1: convert string to char array and loop through each character
for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
    count++;   // Step 2: increment count for each character
}

// Step 3: print result
System.out.println("Length of string: " + count);



ğŸ“ Notes

toCharArray() â†’ breaks string into characters

Loop counts all characters â†’ length

TC: O(n)

SC: O(n) â†’ char array

Memory hook: â€œLoop + count â†’ total chars = lengthâ€
